# Group B Project Structure

The project folder structure follows a feature based approach.

For example, all components related to the student dashboard would sit under the studentDashboard folder. Hooks (component specific), CSS, and tests that relate to the component would also belong in this folder.

`common` is for storing components that are used across multiple pages/dashboards, for example the navigation, header, tables, forms, filters etc. Likewise, their style sheets (CSS), tests etc. would sit in this folder.

`hooks` - for custom hooks that are used by multiple components.

'utils` - General utility functions used across the app (ex. date formatting)

`types` - Define data types that our components consume through props

`services` - API fetching 

`pages` - page-level components that use components from feature/ (ex. studentDashboard/) and common (Navigation bar etc.) 
